  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Logistics Manager",
  "description": "<p>Seeking a highly motivated and experienced <strong>Logistics Manager</strong> to oversee and manage end-to-end logistics operations. This role involves a combination of <strong>hands-on delivery work</strong>, <strong>full office and administrative responsibilities</strong>, <strong>collection and dispatch coordination</strong>, <strong>new business opportunity development</strong>, and <strong>workforce recruitment and management</strong>. The position requires the ability to handle complex, fast-paced operations while ensuring efficiency, accuracy, and customer satisfaction.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Manage daily logistics operations including <strong>collection, delivery, dispatch, and transportation planning</strong></p></li><li><p>Perform <strong>personal delivery and collection tasks</strong> when required to meet operational needs</p></li><li><p>Oversee <strong>office operations</strong>, including documentation, invoicing, scheduling, reporting, and system updates</p></li><li><p>Coordinate dispatch activities to ensure timely and accurate delivery of goods</p></li><li><p>Monitor inventory movement, shipment status, and delivery performance</p></li><li><p>Identify and develop <strong>new business opportunities</strong>, clients, and logistics service improvements</p></li><li><p>Liaise with customers, suppliers, and partners to maintain strong working relationships</p></li><li><p>Recruit, select, and onboard <strong>new workers</strong>, including drivers and operational staff</p></li><li><p>Train, supervise, and evaluate staff performance to ensure compliance with company standards</p></li><li><p>Handle complex operational issues, problem-solving, and process improvements</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with safety regulations, company policies, and industry standards</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Proven experience in <strong>logistics, transport, or supply chain management</strong></p></li><li><p>Ability to manage both <strong>hands-on field work</strong> and <strong>office-based administrative duties</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong organizational, planning, and multitasking skills</p></li><li><p>Experience in <strong>staff recruitment, supervision, and team management</strong></p></li><li><p>Business development or sales experience is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Good communication and customer service skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and handle complex operational responsibilities</p></li><li><p>Proficient in basic computer applications and logistics systems</p></li><li><p>Valid driving licence preferred</p></li></ul><h3>Personal Attributes</h3><ul><li><p>Responsible, reliable, and proactive</p></li><li><p>Strong problem-solving mindset</p></li><li><p>Ability to work under pressure and meet deadlines</p></li><li><p>Willingness to take ownership of end-to-end logistics operations</p></li></ul>",
